<paragraph id="8BAC36C3FFC9FFA7AC06FB6EFE0BFA7E" blockId="8.[111,647,1135,1700]" pageId="8" pageNumber="603">
The 
<typeStatus id="54A88861FFC9FFA7ACEAFB6EFF0FFB50" box="[157,245,1166,1193]" pageId="8" pageNumber="603">holotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus id="54A88861FFC9FFA7AD30FB6EFE67FB50" box="[327,413,1166,1193]" pageId="8" pageNumber="603">paratype</typeStatus>
MNHN-IC.2008-007 were associated with hydroids, which were attached at the tips of a few branches. While the sister taxon 
<taxonomicName id="4C134D40FFC9FFA7AC06FB0EFEDEFAFE" baseAuthorityName="Wright &amp; Studer" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[113,292,1261,1287]" class="Anthozoa" family="Chrysogorgiidae" genus="Metallogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="603" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="melanotrichos">
<emphasis id="B967EAD1FFC9FFA7AC06FB0EFEDEFAFE" box="[113,292,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="603">M. melanotrichos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in close association with 
<taxonomicName id="4C134D40FFC9FFA7AC07FAEDFE4DFAD1" authority="Lyman, 1879" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1879" box="[112,439,1293,1320]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Euryalidae" genus="Ophiocreas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euryalida" pageId="8" pageNumber="603" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="oedipus">
<emphasis id="B967EAD1FFC9FFA7AC07FAEDFED0FADE" box="[112,298,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="603">Ophiocreas oedipus</emphasis>
Lyman, 1879
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF824B32FFC9FFA7ADB4FAEDFF53FAB1" author="MOSHER C. &amp; WATLING L." pageId="8" pageNumber="603" refId="ref9217" refString="MOSHER C. &amp; WATLING L. 2009. - Partners for life: a brittle star and its octocoral host. Marine Ecology-Progress Series 397: 81 - 88. DOI: 10.3354 / meps 08113." type="book" year="2009">Mosher &amp; Watling 2009</bibRefCitation>
), no brittle stars were observed on the colonies examined (however, the symbionts might have been separated during or after sampling).
</paragraph>
